SUCH SWAPS ALLOW THE COMPANY TO EFFECTIVELY CONVERT FIXED-RATE PAYMENTS INTO FLOATING-RATE PAYMENTS OR FLOATING-RATE PAYMENTS INTO FIXED-RATE PAYMENTS. IN THE THIRD QUARTER OF 2014, THE COMPANY ENTERED INTO INTEREST RATE SWAPS WITH AN AGGREGATE

NOTIONAL AMOUNT OF $9.0 BILLION, WHICH EFFECTIVELY CONVERTED THE FIXED-RATE NOTES DUE 2017, 2019, 2021 AND 2024 INTO FLOATING-RATE NOTES. IN THE THIRD QUARTER OF 2013, THE COMPANY ENTERED INTO INTEREST RATE SWAPS WITH AN AGGREGATE NOTIONAL

AMOUNT OF $3.0 BILLION, WHICH EFFECTIVELY CONVERTED THE FLOATING-RATE NOTES DUE 2016 AND 2018 INTO FIXED-RATE NOTES.

